ce:section.ce:para:
The crystalline structures of the materials were analyzed using the XRD technique (
                           Fig. S4
                        ). The characteristic diffraction peaks mainly appeared in the 2θ range of 5–65°. The diffraction peaks observed in the pattern of N-GQDs@MIP@MIL-101 were similar to those in the spectra of N-GQDs and MIL-101, demonstrating that the composite materials retained their crystal structures in the synthesized probe. These results further confirmed the successful formation of the probe.
